news.title: Irregularities in allotment of Amritsar plots: Punjab vigilance bureau
news.para: A press release issued by the bureau said during the probe, evidence was found of alleged connivance of officers and employees of AIT in the allotment of commercial and residential plots.

news.title: Lodha Developers to invest Rs 3,950 crore over 5-7 years on sustainability initiatives
news.para: Lodha said: "Over the next five to seven years, we will be spending almost USD 500 million to ensure that our developments are moving to the net-zero carbon goal that we have".

news.title: PE investment in Indian real estate touch Rs 56 billion in Q2 2022: Savills India
news.para: As per the data, much like the previous quarter, commercial office assets continued to claim the lion’s share, of the PE investment during Q2 2022.

news.title: Awfis and Nucleus Office Parks launch 27,000 sq ft space in Mumbai
news.para: The Mumbai centre has been launched in partnership with Nucleus Office Parks, the operating platform for fully owned Blackstone offices in India.

news.title: How green zone dilution in draft Delhi-NCR plan 2041 defied objections
news.para: Of the objections and suggestions it received on the draft - a critical policy paper because it sets the contours of how the region will develop over the next two decades, balancing ecology and development - 95% were on the proposal altering 'natural conservation zones (NCZ)' to 'natural zones (NZ)'.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board demolishes 17 illegal structures in 20 days
news.para: These structures were demolished at Ram Darbar, Daddumajra and Sector 45. Officials recently submitted a progress report on these demolitions.

news.title: Gurugram: Nine societies told to get regular power connections by Aug 31
news.para: The aim is to control the use of diesel generators before the graded response action plan (GRAP) kicks in across Delhi-NCR, officials said.

news.title: Complete all houses as per schedule: Andhra Pradesh CM
news.para: Speaking to the officials at the review, the chief minister directed them to follow the Standard Operating Procedure (SoP) to expedite the construction works for those who choose Option 3.

news.title: Delhi LG launches scheme to reward RWAs for property tax compliance
news.para: The scheme will incentivise RWAs on achieving 90 per cent tax collection from total number of properties in their societies or colonies, allowing them to recommend development work to the tune of 10 per cent of the collected tax amount, with a cap of Rs one lakh, said a statement from LG office.

news.title: Why not auction directors' properties: Amrapali homebuyers take to Twitter
news.para: In a circular uploaded on the court receiver’s website, the committee said that the corpus would help deal with the shortage of funds in the future.

news.title: Leasing of office space at record 18.2 million sq ft in top nine cities in Q2 2022: CBRE
news.para: CBRE said that the absorption in H1 (January-June) 2022 rose 158 per cent annually to touch 29.5 million square feet as compared to H1 2021.

news.title: ABIL group chairman to now stay in ED custody till July 21
news.para: The ED produced Bhosale in court and informed that since he is an influential person, he may hamper the ongoing investigation if released from custody.

news.title: Sagar Cements seen leading race for Jaypee Group's Andhra Cements
news.para: Andhra Cements' lenders received expressions of interest from Sagar Cements, B C Jindal's Jindal Poly Films, Dalmia Cement (Bharat) Ltd and Khandwala Finstock Pvt Ltd, according to a stock exchange disclosure.

news.title: Amrapali homebuyers to pay extra to meet shortfall?
news.para: Noting that the cost of construction has increased substantially since initial booking of the unit was made by homebuyers a decade ago, a separate "Sinking cum Reserve Fund" has been created where the homebuyers would deposit the additional amount.

news.title: Vibrations from Supertech twin towers demolition unlikely to cause damage: Study
news.para: Officials said the Vibrock report was on Monday shared with the Noida Authority, the developer Supertech and CBRI. The twin towers — Apex and Ceyane — are set to be demolished on August 21.
